# Governance System

Read `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_SPEC.md` §10 for complete code patterns.

## Epoch Lifecycle
1. Epoch N active with weight vector [recency, engagement, bridging, source_diversity, relevance]
2. Voting period opens (status = 'voting')
3. Subscribers cast votes via `POST /api/governance/vote`
4. Voting closes when: period expires OR manual trigger
5. Aggregate votes → trimmed mean per component → normalize to sum=1.0
6. Transaction: close Epoch N → create Epoch N+1 with new weights → audit log
7. Next scoring pipeline run picks up new weights automatically

## Vote Aggregation (Trimmed Mean)
- Sort votes per component, remove top 10% and bottom 10% outliers
- Take mean of remaining votes per component
- Normalize resulting vector to sum to 1.0
- Minimum vote threshold: configurable (default 5 votes, env: GOVERNANCE_MIN_VOTES)

## Validation Rules
- Voter MUST be an active subscriber (exists in subscribers table, last_seen recent)
- Each weight component must be 0.0-1.0
- All 5 weights must sum to 1.0 (tolerance: 0.01, then normalize)
- One vote per voter per epoch (upsert — last vote wins)
- All votes logged to governance_audit_log

## Audit Log (APPEND-ONLY)
- Event types: epoch_created, vote_cast, vote_updated, epoch_closed, weights_changed
- NEVER update or delete audit log rows
- Store: event_type, actor_did, epoch_id, details (JSONB), created_at
- This is the trust anchor — voters verify their votes were counted

## Authentication
- MVP: Bluesky app password authentication (prove DID ownership)
- Upgrade path: Bluesky OAuth flow
- Session: JWT or signed cookie after DID verification
